x4freetext: TARGETS OF METALLIC CA WERE PREPARED BY EVAPORATION
FROM A BAFFIED TANTALUM OVEN CONTAINING A MIXTURE OF
ISOTOPICALLY ENRICHED CACO(3) AND TANTALUM POWDER.
THE CACO(3)USED IN THE PREPARATION OF THE CA-44 TARGETS
WAS ENRICHED TO 98.55% IN CA-44.THE TARGET WAS
DEPOSITED ONTO A 0.25MM TANTALUM SUBSTRATE AND ALLOWED
TO OXIDIZE FULLY IN AIR BEFORE BOMBARDMENT.
THE CROSS SECTION HAVE BEEN DEDUCED FROM GAMMA-RAYS
YIELD.

FROM A BAFFIED TANTALUM OVEN CONTAINING A MIXTURE OF
ISOTOPICALLY ENRICHED CACO(3) AND TANTALUM POWDER.
THE CACO(3)USED IN THE PREPARATION OF THE CA-42 TARGETS
WAS ENRICHED TO 94.42% IN CA-42.THE TARGET WAS
DEPOSITED ON ETCHED TUNGSTEN BACKING AND WAS
TRANSFERRED TO THE TARGET CHAMBER UNDER ARGON TO
MINIMIZE OXIDATION BECAUSE THICK,OXIDISED CA TARGETS
TO PEEL OFF THE BACKING.
